Sentencas: Fine-microstructure mediated efficient hydrogen oxidation was demonstrated on nickel/yttria-stabilised zirconia (Nil YSZ) anode fabricated from NiO/YSZ nanocomposite particles, synthesised via a novel co-precipitation method using YSZ nanoparticles with the average size of 3 nm.
Titulo: Fine-microstructure Mediated Efficient Hydrogen Oxidation in Ni/YSZ Anode Fabricated from Novel Co-precipitation Derived Nanocomposites

Sentencas: Transmission electron microscopy image revealed that nanocomposite particles calcined at 600 degrees C consisted of homogeneously distributed NiO and YSZ nanocrystals, approximately 5 nm large.
Titulo: Fine-microstructure Mediated Efficient Hydrogen Oxidation in Ni/YSZ Anode Fabricated from Novel Co-precipitation Derived Nanocomposites

Sentencas: The Ni/YSZ anode was fabricated by sintering the screen-printed nanocomposites at 1,300 degrees C and their subsequent reduction.
Titulo: Fine-microstructure Mediated Efficient Hydrogen Oxidation in Ni/YSZ Anode Fabricated from Novel Co-precipitation Derived Nanocomposites

Sentencas: The anode had a uniform porous microstructure consisting of fine grains in the range of 200-300 nm, and exhibited quite low area-specific resistance (ASR) of 2.29, 0.43 and 0.15 Omega cm(2) at 600, 700 and 800 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Fine-microstructure Mediated Efficient Hydrogen Oxidation in Ni/YSZ Anode Fabricated from Novel Co-precipitation Derived Nanocomposites
